                <h3>What is a low-season discount?</h3>
                <p>A low-season or off-season discount is a special offer made available to travellers to incentivise them to travel to locations which are typically avoided by them during specific seasons to boost the economy of the area. This is especially common for hill stations which offer discounts encouraging travellers to brave the chill of winter.</p>

                <h3>What was the first airlines to use a frequent flyer program?</h3>
                <p>The first airlines to use a frequent flyer program was the United Airlines of the United States of America. The airlines first developed this system as we know it in the latter half of the last century in 1972. It worked by providing travellers who frequently used the airlines with a plaque that distinguished them and other promotional materials.</p>
